# Copy to `.dev.vars` for local development (`wrangler dev` loads it automatically).
# `.dev.vars` is git-ignored. In production these are set as Wrangler secrets /
# GitHub Actions secrets. Nightingale runs in a degraded-but-working "tier 3"
# mode with NONE of these set (deterministic scripted scenarios + rendered
# email preview), so an interviewer can always click the link and see it work.

# --- Tier 2: GPT text-chat harness + real agent reasoning ---
OPENAI_API_KEY=""

# --- Tier 1: real ElevenLabs voice widget + tool webhooks ---
# ELEVENLABS_AGENT_ID alone lights up the browser widget (public agent).
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY additionally lets the Worker mint signed URLs (private agents).
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=""
ELEVENLABS_AGENT_ID=""
# Inbound tool-call auth — set ONE and give it to the agent's tool config:
#   WEBHOOK_HMAC_SECRET — verified as an HMAC signature over the request body.
#   WEBHOOK_TOKEN       — matched against the `x-webhook-token` request header
#                         (simplest: set this and add the header in each tool).
WEBHOOK_HMAC_SECRET=""
WEBHOOK_TOKEN=""

# --- Real email confirmations (optional; preview always renders without it) ---
RESEND_API_KEY=""
RESEND_FROM="Nightingale <noreply@your-verified-domain>"

# --- Gated write/admin actions (re-seed DB, edit prompts) ---
ADMIN_TOKEN="change-me-locally"
